1
00:00:08,070 --> 00:00:09,350
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:09,350 --> 00:00:10,910
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:14,360
(Episode 1)

4
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,080
Our little princess,

5
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:29,760
- Over here!
- Ji Ni, over here!

6
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:32,640
- So pretty!
- Ji Ni, look here!

7
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:35,520
- Pretty!
- Great!

8
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:42,600
Only good things from now on, Ji Ni!

9
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:45,800
Only red carpets for you!

10
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:50,360
It was a mild day, and I was happy.

11
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:22,280
I had every reason to be happy.

12
00:01:25,170 --> 00:01:29,160
Everyone said I was born
with a silver spoon in my mouth.

13
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,440
- Nothing beats ramen after the academy!
- Exactly!

14
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:39,520
- Right!
- I saw him. He was so handsome.

15
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:40,720
I don't want to study.

16
00:01:40,730 --> 00:01:43,080
I told her to skip the academy and pay
for my plastic surgery instead.

17
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:44,760
My mom totally wastes her money.

18
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:48,280
I'm so jealous of kids who are born rich.

19
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:49,800
Right, me too.

20
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,160
If I'm born rich in my next life,

21
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,960
I'll get my face fixed first.

22
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,640
- Hey, let's go together.
- Right.

23
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,480
She's so pretty.

24
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,440
Hey, she's really pretty.

25
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,280
You couldn't look like that in 100 years.

26
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,120
- Hey, no! Give it back!
- I'll just use it for a second.

27
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,120
- Hold still.
- Give it back. It's mine!

28
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,600
I'll throw it away!

29
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:22,750
That's mine! Don't touch it!
Help! Somebody help me!

30
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,840
Shut up!

31
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:32,520
- What are you doing?
- Help me!

32
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,040
What?

33
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:17,600
- Thank you.
- Learn how to protect yourself.

34
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,520
- Stop obsessing over being born rich.
- What?

35
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,360
- That's...
- Don't walk alone next time!

36
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,560
You're weak, and you're not even scared?

37
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,560
She's amazing.

38
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:33,370
(Liebe Vocal Class)

39
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:14,720
Everything has a shadow
as large as itself.

40
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,600
So do I.

41
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:38,920
(Family Register)

42
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,880
What?

43
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:45,220
Why do you both look so exhausted?

44
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,240
Thank you, Boss.

45
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,720
We'll enjoy it.

46
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:52,320
Unbelievable.
You think I'm a pushover, right?

47
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,920
What kind of employee yawns
without covering their mouth?

48
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,520
I had no hand to cover it with.

49
00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:00,360
Fine. This pushover boss
will let it slide.

50
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,000
- Thank you, rich pushover boss.
- Sure.

51
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:08,760
- Were you up all night?
- No, I slept.

52
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,320
I don't know why I'm so tired.

53
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,880
- Fix that attitude.
- What?

54
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:17,310
Just thinking about dinner with your mom
wears you out. Bad daughter.

55
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,640
You know me too well.

56
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,880
Drink some more and get yourself together.

57
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:26,440
- Come on, get up.
- Forget it. What a hassle.

58
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:30,600
Na Ji Ni, hurry up. Come on!

59
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,840
Jeon Jung A, please!

60
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,760
I'm still drinking my coffee!

61
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,960
Come on. Let's go.

62
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,680
What a hassle.

63
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,960
How lovely!

64
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:44,320
I wish Jung A were my daughter.

65
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:48,480
Jung A really is talented.
She even brought flowers!

66
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,520
I absolutely love it.

67
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,840
Then make her your daughter.

68
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,440
But why is no one here?

69
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,000
It's just us today.

70
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:58,280
Mom, you're loaded.

71
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,640
This is why I work so hard,
to do this much for my husband's birthday.

72
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,920
Do beloved wives just fall from the sky?

73
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,760
It takes effort.

74
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,440
Nothing comes for free.

75
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,560
Sure. Of course.

76
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,880
- Can I sit here?
- Wait!

77
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:15,400
Don't sit yet. We have to greet Dad first.

78
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,400
You're so dramatic.

79
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:19,910
Dad!

80
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:24,110
- My goodness!
- Honey!

81
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,600
An angel just came down from the sky.

82
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,520
- Honey, I missed you.
- Honey.

83
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:36,440
Honey, why do you look so handsome today?

84
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,120
- Honey, happy birthday!
- Thank you!

85
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,800
Happy birthday!

86
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:33,040
A dinner with the two women I love most.

87
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:38,240
Right now, I must be
the happiest man in the world.

88
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:44,240
- Honey, let's live to 100!
- Of course.

89
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,320
Honey, that brat doesn't look happy
about us living that long.

90
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:53,880
No, it's fine. Do whatever you want.

91
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:57,280
You're going to do this every birthday
until you're 100. Twice a year.

92
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,480
- Of course.
- Of course.

93
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,000
No, honey.

94
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,320
When Ji Ni gets married, that makes
four times a year with the son-in-law.

95
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:04,340
Right.

96
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,800
Just thinking about it makes me sick.

97
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,800
- Na Ji Ni.
- Count me out.

98
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,520
This kind of thing really isn't for me.

99
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,990
Fine, I'll leave you out.
We'll do it ourselves.

100
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Really?

101
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:17,480
Then make time this weekend.

102
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:18,520
You'll meet someone.

103
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:22,640
- Mom.
- Just meet him first, then decide.

104
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,520
Have you ever seen a catch like this?

105
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,320
He's tall,

106
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:30,360
great family background, what more?
His education? Are you curious?

107
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,680
I'm not scared at all.

108
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,840
This winter, or at the latest
by next spring, I'm getting you married.

109
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,800
You'll get married and go on
family variety shows with me.

110
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:45,320
Honestly, we've been getting
so many casting offers lately.

111
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:46,330
Seriously!

112
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,840
What kind of attitude is that?

113
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,560
- Ji Ni, your mom is...
- Mom, do you even have a conscience?

114
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,680
Who do you think caused all this?

115
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,600
What makes you think
you can tell me to get married?

116
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:01,530
- Will it satisfy you if I fall apart?
- What's wrong with you?

117
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,760
Is there anyone in this world
without flaws?

118
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,400
What flaws does that family have?

119
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:08,160
Is he divorced? Does he have a kid?

120
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,600
Or some kind of past he can't talk about?

121
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,520
Ji Ni, don't jump
to conclusions like that.

122
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:15,920
You want me to be confident? You want me
to believe none of this is my fault?

123
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:21,680
Don't cry. Who's going to care if you cry?

124
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,800
When you say that,
you're the most cowardly, and I hate it.

125
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:30,160
I'm not coming next year. Don't call me.

126
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:33,360
I'm sorry. Okay. Let's stop.

127
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,080
I was wrong. Let's eat.

128
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,480
I'm barely holding myself together.

129
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,000
Don't pretend you've forgotten everything.

130
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:54,280
You know. You remember.

131
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,080
Don't act as if nothing happened.

132
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,680
No one's fooled.

133
00:10:00,690 --> 00:10:01,820
Dad,

134
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,280
happy birthday.

135
00:10:09,570 --> 00:10:10,650
I'm sorry.

136
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,200
Ji Ni!

137
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:38,940
I told you to wait.

138
00:10:38,970 --> 00:10:40,710
Why are you in such a rush?

139
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:43,180
If she gets any older,
she really might not get married.

140
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:46,770
We should marry her
while we're still at our peak.

141
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:51,350
Even if she meets someone now,
they'll need a year to know each other.

142
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:56,600
So we don't have time.
We can't just leave her like this.

143
00:10:56,770 --> 00:10:57,810
Don't worry too much.

144
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:00,390
Let's trust Ji Ni. We should trust her.

145
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:09,380
This is all because of you.

146
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,700
It's all your fault.

147
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:15,500
Yeah.

148
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:17,400
I'm sorry.

149
00:11:28,290 --> 00:11:29,780
The man I love,

150
00:11:30,780 --> 00:11:32,360
loving me back,

151
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,640
that's what every woman
in the world wants.

152
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:39,980
And I did everything I could for that.

153
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:22,370
Seriously.

154
00:12:22,590 --> 00:12:24,780
Why does this annual event never change?

155
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:29,070
Exactly. I'm sick of it too.
You are too, aren't you?

156
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:32,660
- Isn't my mom seriously exhausting?
- No, you're the exhausting one.

157
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,710
Your mom is doing her best for you.

158
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:37,180
- What exactly are you unhappy about?
- You wouldn't understand.

159
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:39,020
That's why you don't get it.

160
00:12:39,210 --> 00:12:40,830
Then help me understand.

161
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:41,970
What am I missing?

162
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:43,950
What's the story? Is she your stepmom?

163
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,020
Do you love your dad?
Is your mom your rival or something?

164
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,030
- Jeon Jung A!
- I'm not smart enough to do any better.

165
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:50,680
I seriously can't imagine it.

166
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:52,890
What is it then?

167
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:54,920
Forget it.

168
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,370
Cheers!

169
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:17,460
Hold on, everyone!

170
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:21,290
As always, we have people
celebrating their birthdays today!

171
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:24,980
Let's celebrate the beautiful Rin
and Hau's birthdays.

172
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:29,210
This one's on their bestie, Mai!

173
00:13:30,930 --> 00:13:33,810
Happy birthday.

174
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:36,010
What is this?

175
00:13:39,330 --> 00:13:41,960
Ready! Let's go!

176
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:48,740
Cheers!

177
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,250
(Enrollment Open for Fabric Art Classes)

178
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,600
Mother.

179
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:31,780
You're up early.

180
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,710
Even when I was raising two sons,

181
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:37,440
neither of them ever stayed out all night
partying at clubs.

182
00:14:38,310 --> 00:14:39,950
You're a mother now.

183
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:42,860
See this? It's all your kids' laundry.

184
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,800
Okay.

185
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,950
That's why I said we should hire help.

186
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:49,720
- My dad said he'd arrange someone.
- Dang Hongok Mai.

187
00:14:49,830 --> 00:14:51,560
I know you're rich.

188
00:14:52,730 --> 00:14:55,500
It's not "Hongok." It's "Ngoc."

189
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,980
Mother, seriously!

190
00:14:57,310 --> 00:15:01,830
Hongok's a type of apple.
Of course, I'm just as pretty.

191
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:04,320
Just hang this up.

192
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,340
Are you back already?

193
00:15:09,170 --> 00:15:11,990
You should've come out sooner.
Your mom caught me.

194
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:17,500
I texted you,
but you still haven't seen it.

195
00:15:17,660 --> 00:15:19,980
Sorry. I fell asleep.

196
00:15:20,130 --> 00:15:22,200
Are you making excuses to my son?

197
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,960
I'm tired.

198
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:28,280
The party was fun,
but this place is so far.

199
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:31,710
Mother, let's move to Gangnam, okay?

200
00:15:37,290 --> 00:15:38,540
Mom.

201
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:41,620
My boy. Come here.

202
00:15:42,190 --> 00:15:44,050
Did you sleep well?

203
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:46,720
Where did you go, Mom?

204
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:49,090
- Where did I go...
- To the library.

205
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:51,310
I told you she went to the library.

206
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,530
I'll get you some milk, O Reum.

207
00:15:55,870 --> 00:15:57,610
Why would you lie like that?

208
00:15:58,230 --> 00:15:59,880
I went to a club.

209
00:16:00,270 --> 00:16:02,280
Dancing and having fun like this.

210
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,980
You should grow up fast
and go to the club with me.

211
00:16:07,190 --> 00:16:08,700
My boy.

212
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:12,350
It'd be nice if you grew up fast
and went to clubs.

213
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,670
Grow up fast,
so we can go to clubs together.

214
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,680
Where did the daughter-in-law go,

215
00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:20,760
who begged us to let her marry into
a Korean household?

216
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:23,380
Now she just wants to move
every time we meet.

217
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:25,410
Mai just loves parties.

218
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,260
She's cute.

219
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:29,450
Her family's house is huge
in Ho Chi Minh City.

220
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:33,260
If you want to move to Gangnam,
go ahead without me.

221
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:36,130
- I'm not going.
- I can't go without you either.

222
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:38,890
Honey!

223
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:40,280
Yeah, I'm done.

224
00:16:44,190 --> 00:16:45,650
Pick one.

225
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:48,120
Be the eldest son, or be a husband.

226
00:17:07,130 --> 00:17:08,470
(Love your enemies.)

227
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,470
It's so hot.

228
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,880
I must've sold out my country
in a past life.

229
00:17:19,590 --> 00:17:21,780
I must've committed treason many times.

230
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,680
That's the only explanation for my life.

231
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:30,660
Seung Woo never calls when he's filming.

232
00:17:34,530 --> 00:17:35,540
(My Beloved Pain in the Neck 2)

233
00:17:37,170 --> 00:17:38,470
Who is this?

234
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:42,490
Who are you,
calling another man's woman this early?

235
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:44,990
Are you upset again, Yeong Ju?

236
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:47,300
I only missed one night.

237
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,790
"One night?"

238
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:50,350
You never call whenever you're filming.

239
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,460
Mom,

240
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:54,270
how many times do I have to tell you?
Assistant directors are always shampooing.

241
00:17:54,870 --> 00:17:57,400
I'm so busy I barely have time to breathe.
You want me to call while shampooing?

242
00:17:57,510 --> 00:18:00,070
And what do you mean,
"another man's woman?"

243
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:02,250
You're my woman, Mom.

244
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:05,440
Quit acting all sweet, and be careful.

245
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:07,380
I'll let it slide this once
because of the pregnancy,

246
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,360
- but don't expect it again.
- I know.

247
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:12,410
How many times are you going to say that?

248
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:16,800
Your younger son,

249
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:19,640
is purer than fresh snow.

250
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,870
He's Prince Charming.

251
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:24,720
Yeah.

252
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:27,100
I'm working late today,

253
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,120
so I'll either come home at dawn
or tomorrow morning.

254
00:18:29,730 --> 00:18:30,820
Yeong Ju.

255
00:18:30,870 --> 00:18:33,610
Don't go looking at other guys.

256
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:35,240
You'd better only think about me.

257
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,560
Okay?

258
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:40,170
Was that your mom?

259
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:41,860
Who else would it be?

260
00:18:46,390 --> 00:18:49,590
I think your mom just said
we shouldn't be doing this.

261
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:50,930
We're getting married anyway.

262
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:52,950
I'll introduce you to her soon.

263
00:18:54,870 --> 00:18:56,780
Yes, Professor. I'm looking at it now.

264
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,410
You're right.

265
00:18:59,870 --> 00:19:01,170
It's not a rejection.

266
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:03,660
Yes, I'll contact you
during the installation.

267
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,310
Okay.

268
00:19:09,150 --> 00:19:10,310
Did you call him?

269
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,360
Why is Professor Bae looking for you
all of a sudden?

270
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:14,260
He wants me to work part-time.

271
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:16,140
He became an event coordinator.

272
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,620
That's great.

273
00:19:18,990 --> 00:19:20,220
Let me know if you need an extra hand.

274
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:23,240
- Really?
- You've helped me out plenty at the cafĂ©.

275
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:24,710
I owe you one.

276
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:26,770
- Let's go.
- Okay.

277
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:30,580
- Let's go.
- Yeah, let's go.

278
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:03,620
You're here.

279
00:20:05,670 --> 00:20:07,600
- Hello.
- Hi.

280
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,470
- Hello.
- You're here early.

281
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:10,660
Yes.

282
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:15,760
Ms. Yeong Ju, this academy has
such a nice name.

283
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,080
Lovely, isn't it?

284
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,320
Liebe means love.

285
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:23,360
We sing when we fall in love,
and when love leaves us hurt.

286
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,840
It means this is a place,

287
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,320
where you can sing freely, for any reason.

288
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:30,400
Shall we warm up our voices first?

289
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,520
Good. Focus your sound
with head and nasal resonance,

290
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:42,400
then we'll begin with our first song.

291
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:44,800
(Liebe Vocal Class)

292
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,760
My goodness.

293
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,600
You shouldn't laugh
just because someone makes a mistake.

294
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:07,600
Try singing it softly.

295
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:10,920
Have you forgotten how you all sounded
when you first learned this song?

296
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,160
Even so.

297
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:14,320
We're singing because it's fun,

298
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:16,560
not to enter a competition,

299
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,800
so everyone, relax.

300
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:20,150
I'm sorry.

301
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,920
You could at least practice.

302
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,240
If you're sorry,
treat us to coffee next time.

303
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:26,800
Yes, I'll treat everyone
to snacks next time.

304
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,160
- No, that's not necessary.
- No.

305
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,310
I want to.

306
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,840
(Brother)

307
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:52,560
Joong Bin.

308
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:57,520
What else would I be doing?
Making herbal tonic pills. A movie?

309
00:21:57,760 --> 00:22:00,320
Yes. If you don't have plans tonight,
let's watch a movie.

310
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,320
Is that tonight?

311
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,090
You can't cancel that.
It's more important.

312
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,640
I'll cancel the movie. Go ahead.

313
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,400
Do your best.

314
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:15,230
Please just get married already.

315
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,200
I don't want to go.

316
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:33,000
How many times have you watched this?

317
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:41,640
Be quiet. Where are your manners?

318
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,560
It's an old movie.

319
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,640
Without movies like this,

320
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,320
I wouldn't have married you.

321
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:51,040
True. The Navy was at its peak then.

322
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,280
Sorry.

323
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:06,970
I'm sorry, sir.

324
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:09,040
Sir, Assemblyman Kim is looking for you.

325
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:12,880
"Assemblyman Kim?" Got it.
Honey, I'm sorry.

326
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,300
So annoying. This totally ruined my mood.

327
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,570
Does a family have to be formed
through marriage?

328
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,690
The goal of this curation is ownership.

329
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,680
We plan to place cohesive artworks
in the hotel rooms and venues,

330
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,920
where representatives
from each country will be staying.

331
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:39,840
As outlined in the materials provided,
K-family, K-culture, K-art.

332
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:43,040
We've prepared editions from
the most sought-after blue-chip artists.

333
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:47,340
So this isn't just about viewing,
but leading into collecting as well?

334
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,520
You've seen right through me.
That's correct.

335
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:53,880
Mr. Im Ji Hu,
I fully support your meticulous plan.

336
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,800
Sir, hiring that young specialist
must be rewarding.

337
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:00,950
The honor is mine.
Thank you for giving me this opportunity.

338
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,560
Thank you, everyone, for your support.

339
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,400
Yes, that's good.

340
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:13,200
Just a little bit here.

341
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,000
Yes, that's perfect.

342
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,880
Thank you.

343
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:23,980
Yes, Professor.

344
00:24:24,410 --> 00:24:27,410
I've just finished the work
at the Bang Bae Dong hotel. Yes.

345
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:29,360
The work is complete.

346
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:32,200
- Thank you for your hard work.
- Thank you.

347
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,600
I'll see you tomorrow
at the hotel I mentioned earlier.

348
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:35,640
Yes, understood.

349
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:37,560
- Goodbye.
- Yeah.

350
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,520
- Did Professor Bae write this?
- No.

351
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:57,480
Yes.

352
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:01,120
I wrote it, and Professor Bae approved it.

353
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,040
"A complete family
that includes imperfections."

354
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,320
That's a good line. Well done.

355
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,230
I'm the overall coordinator
requested by Professor Bae.

356
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:18,040
I see.

357
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,040
The doors are closing.

358
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,640
Hold on.

359
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,160
The doors are opening.

360
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,600
Are you Professor Bae's assistant?

361
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:50,920
Yes. I've graduated now.

362
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:04,650
Jung A, I'm done for today.

363
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:08,240
- Really?
- Yeah.

364
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:11,600
It disappeared, but a talented person
from abroad brought it back!

365
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,840
Our group chat is blowing up.

366
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,520
Do you know who he is?

367
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,160
You wouldn't know.

368
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:19,680
Anyway, he was one of the hottest guys
at the arts high school.

369
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,720
Hurry up. The deadline's in two days.

370
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:23,980
"In two days?"

371
00:26:24,630 --> 00:26:26,310
That's way too soon.

372
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:27,840
And we have to see the real thing already?

373
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:30,210
I'm going to lose it, seriously.

374
00:26:30,570 --> 00:26:32,290
Okay, I'm coming right over.

375
00:26:32,790 --> 00:26:34,030
Yeah.

376
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:39,920
It's the first floor. Doors are opening.

377
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,840
How are we supposed to finish this
by the day after tomorrow?

378
00:26:48,230 --> 00:26:49,510
Bathroom.

379
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:57,560
- Ji Hu!
- You got here fast.

380
00:26:57,760 --> 00:27:00,920
Of course! I was so excited for omakase,
my feet just carried me here.

381
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:05,160
You look really good today.

382
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:06,640
- Really?
- Yeah.

383
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:07,760
Want me to take your picture?

384
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,650
Enough with the pictures already.

385
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,120
Stop nagging.

386
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:14,100
Did they renovate this hotel or something?

387
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,800
- I think it's been a while.
- Really?

388
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,960
Hey, what do I do?

389
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:30,160
(Family Register)

390
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:32,160
- I'm Do Do Hee.
- I'm Na Ji Ni.

391
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,160
Let's be friends.

392
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,400
Is beating Na Ji Ni really that hard?

393
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:37,240
You're the problem!

394
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,240
Is cellist Na Se Ri really your mom?

395
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:42,680
- I told you it was a secret.
- That was only before it affected me.

396
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,280
Leave me alone.

397
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:46,400
Do I look like your slave?
Stop harassing me.

398
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:49,080
No one goes after someone like
that unless they mean it.

399
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:51,760
Why me?

400
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:57,060
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
